    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Yainer Diaz** (72.43) and **Taylor Ward** (71.19) headline our lineup, both benefiting from highly favorable park factors and exploitable matchups against vulnerable arms. **Yainer Diaz** sits in a prime spot against Young, where a 16% park boost and positive platoon leverage elevate his floor significantly. Meanwhile, **Taylor Ward** faces a high-xERA opponent in McCullers Jr.; his 19% boost from the SP skill profile and a +8% order advantage make him our strongest outfield play. **Bryson Stott** (70.89) is also a standout, utilizing an elite 13% dynamic platoon edge to overcome any concerns regarding his opponent's battery efficiency, positioning him as a high-upside utility play.\n\nWe are keeping a close eye on the bottom of the order where **Jeremiah Jackson** (68.45) provides sneaky value. Despite hitting 9th, his ability to exploit a slow delivery from McCullers Jr. to steal a base\u2014our scarcest category\u2014makes him a strategic play over more conventional options. The closest call on the bench was **Jung Hoo Lee** (41.36), who narrowly missed the starting cut; while his park factor was positive, the negative platoon friction against Mayza proved too heavy to overcome, pushing him just below the threshold required to displace our current starters.\n\nManagers must proceed with caution regarding the top of the order against elite arms. **Masyn Winn** (42.21) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (45.62) are starting today, but their scores are dragged down by significant -19% SP skill penalties against Skenes and Woodruff, respectively. While **Geraldo Perdomo** gains a +10% order boost for leading off, he remains a marginal start. We are essentially relying on his sprint speed to manufacture value in a tough matchup. Monitor the wind reports for the games involving **Masyn Winn** and **Tyler Freeman**, as the \"Wind Out\" factor is currently providing a slight, necessary cushion to their projected efficiency. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** and **Cal Raleigh** remain inactive due to scheduled off-days, and we continue to rotate **Jonathan Aranda**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Wenceel Perez**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert** based on platoon volatility.",
